::: {.figure-caption}
One simulated holdout, reviewed weekly for a year; the y-axis clips the very wide intervals of the first weeks. The confidence sequence is constructed for simultaneous coverage across all reviews, while the ordinary interval is calibrated for one prespecified review.
:::

After a year, this holdout reports a confidence sequence of
\[0\.18%\, 1\.82%\] and an ordinary interval of \[0\.47%\, 1\.53%\]. One
path shows how the intervals evolve, but not how often either method misses the
true lift. Across the 100 simulated holdouts, we
record whether each interval has contained the true lift at every review so
far:

